<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-155-338  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 155 338.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Computers  March 1989 v38 n3 p356(10).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Dynamic testing strategy for distributed systems. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Meyer, Fred j.; Pradhan, Dhiraj K.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A dynamic testing methodology is developed that enables periodicfault analysis of distributed systems with minimal overhead.andP;  Thetesting model is singly-invalidating, singly-complete andsymmetrically-invalidating.andP;  The test scheduling strategy enablesthe amount of testing performed to be independent of system faulttolerance.andP;  Diagnostic information is gained through messagingbetween processors that are able to test neighboring processors.andO;This testing structure can be represented by a directed graph andis equal to the communication structure between processors.andO;Testing overhead is specifically reduced by the elimination of thecapability of diagnosing any discovered faults.andP;  Details of thedevelopment and validation of the testing methodology aredescribed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Distributed SystemsTestingFailure AnalysisMethodsNew TechniqueResearch and DevelopmentSelf-Test CapabilityCost Reduction.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Application of TFORMER. (chart)Application of LFINDER3. (chart)Diagnosing the disconnecting fault. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>